      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA software is under formal configuration management with documented version control and regression test suite.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2023 R2 is used under a validated software environment. Configuration management records confirm version locking, and the regression test suite covers all element types used in this model. Achieved Gradation 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification performed against benchmark problems with known analytical solutions for beam bending and contact mechanics.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical was verified against NAFEMS benchmarks LE1 and LE10 for linear elasticity and against Hertzian contact solutions for the screw-rod interface. Errors within 0.5% of analytical solutions for all benchmarks."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change of less than 2% between successive refinements.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed on the screw shank and rod cross-section. Stiffness QoI changed by 1.7% between medium and fine meshes; yield force QoI changed by 1.3%. Richardson extrapolation confirms discretization error below 2% threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals documented and confirmed below 1e-6 for all load steps.",
      "rationale": "Sparse direct solver (SPARSE) employed for linear steps; iterative GMRES with ILU preconditioner for nonlinear contact steps. Residual norms confirmed below 1e-6 for all 47 load increments across the three QoI evaluations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent technical review of model setup, boundary conditions, and load application by a second qualified analyst.",
      "rationale": "An independent analyst reviewed the model setup documentation, boundary condition assignments, and load application protocols against the ASTM F1717 standard. No discrepancies identified. Review documented in internal report CR-2025-041."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions documented and justified; sensitivity analysis performed for key modeling choices including contact formulation and material constitutive model.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic isotropic material model for Ti-6Al-4V is justified by the predominantly elastic response regime targeted by the QoIs. Augmented Lagrangian contact formulation selected after comparison with penalty method; difference in stiffness QoI was 0.4%. Bilinear plasticity model used for yield force prediction with tangent modulus calibrated from coupon data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters traceable to documented sources; uncertainty in key inputs quantified and propagated.",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs derived from manufacturing drawings (revision G, 2025). Material properties sourced from 2024 coupon testing dataset. Friction coefficient for screw-rod interface set to 0.15 based on literature (ASTM G115 dry Ti-Ti). Parametric uncertainty propagation performed for elastic modulus (±5%) and friction coefficient (±0.05); combined influence on stiffness QoI is ±3.2%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples are production-representative; dimensional inspection records available for all specimens.",
      "rationale": "All 11 test constructs were assembled from production-lot components. Dimensional inspection confirmed screw outer diameter within 7.5 ±0.05 mm and rod diameter within 5.5 ±0.03 mm for all specimens. Sample provenance documented in laboratory notebook LN-2018-F1717-NC."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of loading conditions relevant to the COU, including at minimum two distinct load levels or configurations.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single loading configuration (pure compression-bending per ASTM F1717 Section 8.3) at a single crosshead displacement rate (25 mm/min). The required level of 2 is not achieved because no variation in loading rate or offset distance was explored. This gap is acknowledged and accepted given that ASTM F1717 prescribes a single standard configuration and the COU is limited to standard test conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters are demonstrably equivalent to the experimental conditions; any discrepancies are quantified and shown to have negligible impact on QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions in the FEA model replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry including the 100 mm offset distance and pin-roller support conditions. Measured specimen dimensions were used to parameterize each of the 11 FEA runs. Crosshead displacement rate effects are negligible for quasi-static elastic-plastic analysis confirmed by dynamic amplification factor < 0.001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI differences between FEA and experiment are within pre-specified acceptance bounds for all N=11 specimens; E/uval < 1.96.",
      "rationale": "For all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm): maximum specimen-level deviation 9.1%; population-level E/uval values of 1.41, 1.18, and 1.63, all below the 1.96 threshold. Pre-specified acceptance bounds documented in validation plan VP-2025-NC-001 prior to data unblinding."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs selected for validation are directly relevant to the clinical failure modes of concern and are sensitive to the model parameters being assessed.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force is the primary fatigue-related failure precursor; force at 40 mm displacement bounds catastrophic fracture scenarios. All three QoIs are identified in the device risk analysis (FMEA-2024-SCREW-007) as clinically critical outputs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario matches the COU in terms of device geometry, loading mode, and boundary conditions; any differences are justified.",
      "rationale": "The validation scenario replicates the COU exactly: non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw, ASTM F1717 compression-bending, production-representative constructs. The FEA model validated here is the same model (same mesh topology, same constitutive models, same solver settings) used for the regulatory submission prediction. No extrapolation beyond the validated domain is required."
    }
